        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><supplied reason="lost">Δ</supplied>έκο
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>με χαῖ
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>ρε
                 </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text after Isler 1988</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Farewell Dekomos</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Dekomos is presumably Decimus, and is attested in other Sicilian greek inscriptions, such as <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002952">ISic002952</ref> (Cefalu), and as Dekomia at Syracuse in <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000841">ISic000841</ref></p>
            </div>
